{"parentUuid":"afd1af11-acbc-49cd-b19b-d14992a3d88a","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_016EoCT1YwbTh9cue5ZmJ4bs","toolUseID":"toolu_016EoCT1YwbTh9cue5ZmJ4bs","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:57.602Z","uuid":"26d7ef74-3f1a-48bc-878b-9ae72b653769","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"82e3f286-f932-474f-a966-021a72120549","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016EoCT1YwbTh9cue5ZmJ4bs","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Eden Reforestation Projects 2025 2026 trees planted total impact cost per tree\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Eden Reforestation Projects - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eden_Reforestation_Projects\"},{\"title\":\"Eden Reforestation Projects - Altruist Partners | Your partner for impact\",\"url\":\"https://www.altruistpartners.com/case-studies/eden-reforestation-projects/\"},{\"title\":\"Eden Reforestation Projects - Plant Trees | Save Lives\",\"url\":\"https://sustainabledevelopment.un.org/partnership/?p=31193\"},{\"title\":\"Eden Reforestation Projects | Department of Economic and Social Affairs\",\"url\":\"https://sdgs.un.org/partnerships/eden-reforestation-projects\"},{\"title\":\"Eden Reforestation Projects\",\"url\":\"https://reviewforest.org/planting-projects/eden-reforestation-projects\"},{\"title\":\"Eden Reforestation Projects: Plant Trees | Save Lives | Shared Nation\",\"url\":\"https://www.sharednation.org/products/edenreforestation\"},{\"title\":\"Our Restoration Projects - Eden: People+Planet\",\"url\":\"https://eden-plus.org/projects/\"},{\"title\":\"Plant 25 Trees With Eden Reforestation Projects\",\"url\":\"https://evergreen-capsules.com/en-us/products/plant-25-trees-with-eden-reforestation-projects\"},{\"title\":\"Eden Reforestation Projects: Sowing Seeds of Change in 2023 | ReviewForest\",\"url\":\"https://blog.reviewforest.org/eden-reforestation-projects-sowing-seeds-of-change-in-2023/\"},{\"title\":\"Fighting Extreme Poverty Through Tree Planting | Greenspark\",\"url\":\"https://www.getgreenspark.com/projects/eden-reforestation-projects-fighting-extreme-poverty-through-tree-planting\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results, here's what I found about Eden Reforestation Projects (now known as Eden: People+Planet):\n\n## Total Trees Planted\n\nSince its establishment, Eden has planted over 977 million trees across its project sites. More recently, Eden currently plants approximately 15 million trees a month, though this figure appears to be from an earlier reporting period.\n\n## Cost Per Tree\n\nEden is the world's most efficient reforestation nonprofit, at less than $0.15 per tree.\n\n## Recent Impact and Goals\n\nEden planted 180M trees in 2020; 360M in 2021; and they surpassed a cumulative total of 1 billion in June of 2022. The organization has ambitious expansion plans, with an audacious goal to be the first to plant 1 billion trees, and plant 50 billion by 2030.\n\n## Organizational Status\n\nOn June 13, 2024, the NGO announced it had changed its name to Eden: People+Planet to better represent its broader mission. As of November 2025, Charity Navigator gave Eden a score of 4 out of 4 stars (based on a rating of 94%).\n\nThe search results don't contain specific 2025-2026 projections or data for those particular years, but the most recent information available shows the organization's strong track record and commitment to large-scale reforestation efforts.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"7455cda4-f0d0-499d-8f18-7da7dd98c4e2","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:57.601Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"82e3f286-f932-474f-a966-021a72120549","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"7455cda4-f0d0-499d-8f18-7da7dd98c4e2","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_014bp7BvZHQRsJssFf7amr4q","toolUseID":"toolu_014bp7BvZHQRsJssFf7amr4q","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:59.209Z","uuid":"c5518a64-0ea5-4b82-b7d3-e0e70171d233","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"ac700092-b344-4d22-bf09-ed0e05e230b9","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014bp7BvZHQRsJssFf7amr4q","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Anthropic Economic Futures program 2026 grants AI displacement workers\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Anthropic Economic Futures program\",\"url\":\"https://www.anthropic.com/economic-futures/program\"},{\"title\":\"Economic Futures - Understanding AI’s effects on the economy\",\"url\":\"https://www.anthropic.com/economic-futures\"},{\"title\":\"Preparing for AI's economic impact: exploring policy ...\",\"url\":\"https://www.anthropic.com/research/economic-policy-responses\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic Economic Futures Program Launch\",\"url\":\"https://www.anthropic.com/news/introducing-the-anthropic-economic-futures-program\"},{\"title\":\"As job losses loom, Anthropic launches program to track AI's economic fallout | TechCrunch\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2025/06/27/as-job-losses-loom-anthropic-launches-program-to-track-ais-economic-fallout/\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic Launches Economic Futures Program to Address AI Job Displacement Concerns\",\"url\":\"https://www.ainvest.com/news/anthropic-launches-economic-futures-program-address-ai-job-displacement-concerns-2506/\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic Introduces Economic Futures Program to Address the Economic Impact of AI - InfoQ\",\"url\":\"https://www.infoq.com/news/2025/07/anthropic-economic-program/\"},{\"title\":\"50% of White-Collar Jobs at Risk? Anthropic Is Funding the Research to Find Out\",\"url\":\"https://blog.agent.ai/50-of-white-collar-jobs-at-risk-anthropic-is-funding-the-research-to-find-out\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic's Economic Futures Program: The AI Initiative Aiming to Tackle Job Displacement | AI News\",\"url\":\"https://opentools.ai/news/anthropics-economic-futures-program-the-ai-initiative-aiming-to-tackle-job-displacement\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic’s Economic Futures Program: How AI Research Grants Could Transform the Job Market\",\"url\":\"https://completeaitraining.com/news/anthropics-economic-futures-program-how-ai-research-grants/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Anthropic's Economic Futures program and its approach to AI-related worker displacement:\n\n## Program Overview\n\nThe Anthropic Economic Futures program is a multidisciplinary program funding research grants, policy development, and data infrastructure to help society understand and navigate AI's economic transformation. Launched in June 2025, Anthropic's Economic Futures Program is a $15 million research initiative designed to explore the economic and societal impacts of frontier AI systems.\n\n## Research Grants\n\nEconomic Futures Research Awards will offer grants between $10,000 and $50,000 for empirical research on AI's economic impacts. The grants include $5,000 in Claude API credits for computational analysis. Recipients are asked to present and share their findings within a six-month timeframe after receiving their grant.\n\n## Three Pillars\n\nThe program consists of three interconnected pillars: Through research grants, API credits, and strategic partnerships, they aim to support investigations into AI's impact on labor, productivity, and the economy. The other pillars include policy symposia and data infrastructure development.\n\n## Policy Approaches\n\nSeveral economists are exploring how the Trade Adjustment Assistance (TAA) model – in which affected workers are given opportunities to obtain new skills, or receive other support – might be adapted for labor market disruptions in an era of powerful AI, with economists like Ioana Marinescu viewing TAA-like \"AI insurance\" as a mechanism \"to support those who lose jobs due to AI.\"\n\nThe program appears focused on generating evidence-based research rather than directly providing grants to displaced workers themselves.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"e63c5418-5c2f-4142-8f7c-0792b0f9c8da","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:20:59.209Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ac700092-b344-4d22-bf09-ed0e05e230b9","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
