{"parentUuid":"9d86f0ce-0310-469c-818a-df00e4d5eee4","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_018gQVf8qKeA4N8iiZmkvVjw","toolUseID":"toolu_018gQVf8qKeA4N8iiZmkvVjw","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:14.072Z","uuid":"25c88d81-601e-4e40-971f-ed4fcbb1238a","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"eb2fb7d7-647a-466f-8d4b-3503f5c587c0","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018gQVf8qKeA4N8iiZmkvVjw","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"voluntary carbon market 2025 2026 size growth projections ICVCM Article 6\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"ICVCM Leading the way to a high integrity Voluntary Carbon Market\",\"url\":\"https://icvcm.org/\"},{\"title\":\"Carbon Credit Prices Today: Trends and Forecasts for 2026\",\"url\":\"https://www.regreener.earth/blog/carbon-credit-prices-today-trends-and-forecasts-for-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Carbon Market Trends 2026: Prices, Quality, and the Future of Carbon Credits\",\"url\":\"https://www.sylvera.com/blog/carbon-market-trends\"},{\"title\":\"Voluntary Carbon Market in 2026: Top Forecasts and What They Mean for Investors • Carbon Credits\",\"url\":\"https://carboncredits.com/voluntary-carbon-market-in-2026-top-forecasts-and-what-they-mean-for-investors/\"},{\"title\":\"Voluntary Carbon Market - Latest Prices and Developments | Regreener\",\"url\":\"https://www.regreener.earth/blog/voluntary-carbon-market-update\"},{\"title\":\"Voluntary Carbon Credit Market Growth Driven by 20.59% CAGR by 2035\",\"url\":\"https://www.globalgrowthinsights.com/market-reports/voluntary-carbon-credit-market-121790\"},{\"title\":\"Article 6 and the carbon market: Progress and future | RECOFTC\",\"url\":\"https://www.recoftc.org/stories/article-6-and-carbon-market-progress-and-future\"},{\"title\":\"High-Integrity Carbon Markets Toolkit | UNDP Climate Promise\",\"url\":\"https://climatepromise.undp.org/carbonmarketstoolkit/resources\"},{\"title\":\"Key trends in the 2026 voluntary carbon market | Carbon Direct\",\"url\":\"https://www.carbon-direct.com/insights/key-trends-2026-voluntary-carbon-market\"},{\"title\":\"Voluntary Carbon Credit Market Size and Industry Growth 2035\",\"url\":\"https://www.rootsanalysis.com/reports/voluntary-carbon-market.html\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results, here's what I found regarding the voluntary carbon market size, growth projections, ICVCM standards, and Article 6:\n\n## Market Size and Growth Projections\n\nThere are varying projections for the voluntary carbon market in 2025-2026:\n\nThe Global Voluntary Carbon Credit Market size was USD 2.52 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 3.04 billion in 2026, followed by USD 3.66 billion in 2027 and ultimately USD 16.38 billion by 2035. The market is set to grow at a strong 20.59% rate during 2026–2035.\n\nHowever, Roots Analysis expects the market to reach around USD 1.7 billion in 2026, rising from USD 1.6 billion in 2025, before accelerating sharply to nearly USD 47.5 billion by 2035 with a strong 38% CAGR.\n\n## ICVCM's Role\n\nGrowth is fueled by stricter regulations, new integrity standards like ICVCM's Core Carbon Principles, and surging corporate net-zero commitments. ICVCM's Core Carbon Principles are setting a global quality baseline. Paris Agreement mechanisms are increasingly connecting voluntary and regulatory systems, while countries like Singapore and EU regulators demand credibility and restrict low-quality credits.\n\n## Article 6 Implementation\n\nIt wasn't until COP29 (2024) in Baku that negotiators finalized the rulebook for carbon trading under Article 6.2 (bilateral trading between countries) and 6.4 (a UN-supervised market open to both countries and corporations). This decision paves the way for full operationalization in 2025.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"b9f586bb-c9fd-4e36-8c8c-07513d6963ba","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:14.072Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"eb2fb7d7-647a-466f-8d4b-3503f5c587c0","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"b9f586bb-c9fd-4e36-8c8c-07513d6963ba","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_017vPp3cEFbm6KwpZpk1vmiQ","toolUseID":"toolu_017vPp3cEFbm6KwpZpk1vmiQ","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:14.550Z","uuid":"d0e3faf0-7ae8-48e5-bc8a-a42041cd3dfd","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"d9f398d8-1522-4876-94a7-fe3613048e51","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017vPp3cEFbm6KwpZpk1vmiQ","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Microsoft carbon removal program 2025 2026 billion dollar commitment progress\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Carbon Removal Program | Microsoft CSR\",\"url\":\"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/corporate-responsibility/sustainability/carbon-removal-program\"},{\"title\":\"From farms to oceans: How Microsoft is working to scale carbon dioxide removal - Source\",\"url\":\"https://news.microsoft.com/source/features/sustainability/from-farms-to-oceans-how-microsoft-is-working-to-scale-carbon-dioxide-removal/\"},{\"title\":\"Microsoft Doubles Carbon Removal Agreements to 45 Million Tonnes in 2025 - ESG Today\",\"url\":\"https://www.esgtoday.com/microsoft-doubles-carbon-removal-agreements-to-45-million-tonnes-in-2025/\"},{\"title\":\"Microsoft Kicks Off 2026 With Flurry of Large-Scale Carbon Removal Purchase Deals - ESG Today\",\"url\":\"https://www.esgtoday.com/microsoft-kicks-off-2026-with-flurry-of-large-scale-carbon-removal-purchase-deals/\"},{\"title\":\"Microsoft More Than Doubles Carbon Removal Deals to 45 Million Tonnes in 2025 • Carbon Credits\",\"url\":\"https://carboncredits.com/microsoft-more-than-double-carbon-removal-deals-to-45-million-tonnes-in-2025/\"},{\"title\":\"Microsoft taps India’s Varaha for durable carbon removal offtake | TechCrunch\",\"url\":\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/01/15/microsoft-taps-indias-varaha-for-asia-first-durable-carbon-removal-offtake/\"},{\"title\":\"Carbon Reduction Program | Microsoft CSR\",\"url\":\"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/corporate-responsibility/sustainability/carbon-reduction\"},{\"title\":\"Unpacking Microsoft’s mega-purchases in durable carbon removal\",\"url\":\"https://trellis.net/article/microsoft-durable-carbon-removal/\"},{\"title\":\"Microsoft kicks 2026 off with raft of carbon-removal deals - Real Economy Progress\",\"url\":\"https://real-economy-progress.com/microsoft-kicks-2026-off-with-raft-of-carbon-removal-deals/\"},{\"title\":\"Microsoft is not backing off its 2030 carbon negative climate goal\",\"url\":\"https://trellis.net/article/microsoft-2025-sustainability-report-not-backing-off-climate-goal/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Microsoft's carbon removal program progress in 2025 and 2026:\n\n## Carbon Removal Scale\n\nMicrosoft's carbon dioxide removal agreements in fiscal year 2025 are two times the volume contracted in the preceding fiscal year and nine times the volume contracted in fiscal year 2023. More specifically, Microsoft more than doubled carbon removal in 2025 to 45 million tonnes.\n\n## Recent Major Deals\n\nThe company continued its momentum into 2026 with several significant agreements. In May 2025, Microsoft reached an expanded ten-year agreement with Stockholm Exergi to remove over 5 million metric tonnes of carbon dioxide. In June 2025, Microsoft reached an agreement with Agoro to purchase 2.6 million metric tonnes of carbon dioxide removals over 12 years. In January 2025, re.green and Microsoft reached an expanded agreement to purchase a total of nearly 6.5 million metric tonnes of carbon dioxide and restore a total of 33,000 hectares in the Amazon and Atlantic Forest biomes.\n\nIn early 2026, Microsoft's purchases reached 5 million tonnes in just the first weeks of 2026.\n\n## Financial Investment\n\nMicrosoft does not disclose what it pays for removals, but publicly available pricing data for similar projects puts the cost of its two largest projects alone at more than $2 billion. More broadly, Microsoft has allocated more than $793 million for new climate technologies and is now the largest single buyer of carbon removal credits, worth more than 30 million metric tons.\n\n## Long-Term Commitment\n\nMicrosoft has committed to be carbon negative by 2030, which means reducing greenhouse gas emissions by more than half, removing the rest, and then removing the equivalent of its historical emissions by 2050.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"7a74923e-1164-482a-84f9-bdc2898c9c2c","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:14.550Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"d9f398d8-1522-4876-94a7-fe3613048e51","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"7a74923e-1164-482a-84f9-bdc2898c9c2c","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01TrDjqv1xx9Jrjw2giiHwKZ","toolUseID":"toolu_01TrDjqv1xx9Jrjw2giiHwKZ","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:15.781Z","uuid":"d653dc09-ffa9-4c8c-aea6-29bf8522198e","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"97d6dc74-baa7-4a72-b59e-e849c54938f3","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TrDjqv1xx9Jrjw2giiHwKZ","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Google climate AI projects 2025 2026 carbon sustainability initiatives\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Climate and sustainability\",\"url\":\"https://research.google/teams/climate-and-sustainability/\"},{\"title\":\"Sustainability AI — Google AI\",\"url\":\"https://ai.google/sustainability/\"},{\"title\":\"Energy and Sustainability | Google Public Policy\",\"url\":\"https://publicpolicy.google/sustainability/\"},{\"title\":\"What is Google's Sustainability Strategy, And How Are Channel Partners Involved? - Sustainable Tech Partner for IT Service Providers\",\"url\":\"https://sustainabletechpartner.com/news/google-sustainability-news-milestones-cloud-partnerships-and-net-zero-timeline/\"},{\"title\":\"Google Launches $30M AI for Science Initiative to Advance Climate and Global Research - ESG News\",\"url\":\"https://esgnews.com/google-launches-30m-ai-for-science-initiative-to-advance-climate-and-global-research/\"},{\"title\":\"What Does Google's 2025 Environmental Report Say About AI? | AI Magazine\",\"url\":\"https://aimagazine.com/articles/what-does-google-2025-environmental-report-say-about-tech\"},{\"title\":\"Sustainable Innovation & Technology - Google Sustainability\",\"url\":\"https://sustainability.google/\"},{\"title\":\"Google.org Impact Challenge: AI for Science\",\"url\":\"https://www.google.org/impact-challenges/ai-science/\"},{\"title\":\"The AI opportunity for Europe’s climate goals\",\"url\":\"https://blog.google/company-news/inside-google/around-the-globe/google-europe/ai-climate-policy-europe/\"},{\"title\":\"New report from Google: AI and climate action\",\"url\":\"https://blog.google/company-news/outreach-and-initiatives/sustainability/report-ai-sustainability-google-cop28/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's an overview of Google's climate AI projects and sustainability initiatives for 2025-2026:\n\n## Climate Moonshot Goals\n\nGoogle has set a climate moonshot to run on carbon-free energy, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days a year – by 2030. Additionally, Google has set a climate moonshot to achieve net-zero emissions across all of its operations and value chain by 2030, supported by its ambition to achieve 24/7 carbon-free energy on every grid where it operates.\n\n## Energy and Carbon-Free Initiatives\n\nIn 2024, Google achieved 66% carbon-free energy on average across all of its data centers, and signed contracts for over 8 GW of clean energy. This encompasses projects in solar, wind, nuclear and geothermal energy.\n\nRecent infrastructure investments include Google plans to spend €5.5 billion from 2026 through 2029 on infrastructure and offices in Germany.\n\n## AI for Climate Solutions\n\nGoogle is developing AI innovations that help partners and individuals reduce anthropogenic greenhouse gas in the atmosphere, including AI applications in transportation, energy, and carbon removal.\n\nGoogle estimates that if AI applications become widely adopted they could reduce global energy-related emissions by 4% by 2035, potentially delivering emissions cuts three to five times greater than AI's own projected footprint.\n\n## $30M AI for Science Initiative\n\nGoogle.org has launched a $30M global open-call designed to empower researchers and organizations with funding, tools, and technical expertise to accelerate scientific breakthroughs. Projects must pursue high-impact research in the following areas: AI for Health & Life Sciences, AI for Climate Resilience & Environmental Science. Applications close April 17, 2026.\n\n## Key AI-Powered Applications\n\nIn 2024, five of Google's AI-powered solutions – Nest thermostats, Google Earth Pro, Solar API, fuel-efficient routing in Google Maps and Green Light – removed 26 million metric tons of greenhouse gas emissions.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"9bd4ccc3-4998-49ee-a8ec-833d7beb4883","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:15.781Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"97d6dc74-baa7-4a72-b59e-e849c54938f3","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
