{"parentUuid":"2a7c48fa-3cdb-4960-83be-386693acf63d","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Pg9JiySUnwrTek3SgSu44F","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Gandhian economics trusteeship model modern applications 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Relevance of trusteeship model in modern business world - J Manag Res Anal\",\"url\":\"https://jmra.in/archive/volume/9/issue/1/article/15939\"},{\"title\":\"Trusteeship (Gandhism) - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trusteeship_(Gandhism)\"},{\"title\":\"The Trusteeship Model: A Way Forward to Sustainability – Global Gandhi\",\"url\":\"https://globalgandhi.in/the-trusteeship-model-a-way-forward-to-sustainability/\"},{\"title\":\"Gandhian Economics – GKToday\",\"url\":\"https://www.gktoday.in/gandhian-economics/\"},{\"title\":\"Trusteeship MODEL OF Mahatma Gandhi\",\"url\":\"https://www.amitsachdeva.com/post/trusteeship-model-of-mahatma-gandhi-1\"},{\"title\":\"Trusteeship: Gandhian Approach to Reconceptualize Social Responsibility and Sustainability | SpringerLink\",\"url\":\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-981-99-4008-0_2\"},{\"title\":\"Gandhi: The Non-Violent Socialist is Trusteeship the Only Viable Sustainable Economic Model? | European Journal of Law and Political Science\",\"url\":\"https://www.ej-politics.org/index.php/politics/article/view/15\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) Gandhian Trusteeship and Economic Ethics\",\"url\":\"https://www.academia.edu/44420995/Gandhian_Trusteeship_and_Economic_Ethics\"},{\"title\":\"Gandhian Trusteeship as an 'Instrument of Human Dignity' | Trusteeship | Articles on & By Mahatma Gandhi\",\"url\":\"https://www.mkgandhi.org/articles/trusteeship.php\"},{\"title\":\"Gandhian Trusteeship and Economic Ethics\",\"url\":\"https://ijsred.com/volume3/issue5/IJSRED-V3I5P20.pdf\"}]\n\nI've completed the web search for \"Gandhian economics trusteeship model modern applications 2025.\" Here's a comprehensive overview of the findings:\n\n## Core Concept of Gandhian Trusteeship\n\nTrusteeship is a unique concept advocated by Gandhi to establish social and economic equality. It is a concept that has its origins in spirituality, in which a person voluntarily surrenders his surplus wealth, and entrusts it for the welfare of the poor section of the society.\n\nTrusteeship proposes that wealth and property are not to be owned absolutely but held in trust for the welfare of society. According to this principle, the rich are moral custodians of their wealth and should use their resources to promote social good rather than personal indulgence.\n\n## Modern Applications and Relevance (2025)\n\nIn the twenty-first century, Gandhian economics has regained significance in debates about sustainable development, ethical capitalism, and social justice. The principles of trusteeship, decentralisation, and non-violence resonate with current global efforts to achieve inclusive and ecological growth.\n\nSeveral contemporary movements embody these principles: Movements advocating for local production, fair trade, and minimalism reflect Gandhian ideals in modern contexts. Initiatives like microfinance, cooperative enterprises, and self-help groups also embody the spirit of Gandhian self-reliance and empowerment.\n\n## Connection to Sustainability Goals\n\nThe Gandhian Economics model has already addressed all the elements of SDGs and ESG. The notion of trusteeship unfolds all global challenges and provides a way forward to sustainable and inclusive societies that function in a decentralized manner.\n\n## Real-World Examples\n\nSEWA, founded by Ela Bhatt, is a trade union and women's empowerment organization based in India. SEWA follows the principles of Gandhian trusteeship, advocating for the rights and welfare of women in the informal sector.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"38493d29-6d94-4744-9b16-528e2319c2d0","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:29.192Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"2a7c48fa-3cdb-4960-83be-386693acf63d","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
