{"parentUuid":"a4903e0b-3ea8-4f9b-a8d1-e4ba7a070558","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KF9ibe4LbkuZZUjxUtP8qn","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Jain economics aparigraha non-possession limit consumption sustainable development\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Non-possession - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-possession\"},{\"title\":\"The Three Tenets of Jainism: Implications for Modern Life - MAHB\",\"url\":\"https://mahb.stanford.edu/blog/the-three-tenets-of-jainism-implications-for-modern-life/\"},{\"title\":\"(PDF) Aparigraha: The Jain Philosophy of Non-Possession and Its Ethical Implications in Fostering Minimalism and Sustainable Practices\",\"url\":\"https://www.academia.edu/108441638/Aparigraha_The_Jain_Philosophy_of_Non_Possession_and_Its_Ethical_Implications_in_Fostering_Minimalism_and_Sustainable_Practices\"},{\"title\":\"Aparigraha: The Jain Philosophy of Non-Possession and ...\",\"url\":\"https://www.hansshodhsudha.com/volume4-issue2/1.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"The Core Tenets of Jainism and Sustainable Development - Diplomatist\",\"url\":\"https://diplomatist.com/2025/12/03/the-core-tenets-of-jainism-and-sustainable-development/\"},{\"title\":\"Economic Organization under Jainism - ENCYCLOPEDIA OF JAINISM\",\"url\":\"https://www.en.encyclopediaofjainism.com/index.php/Economic_Organization_under_Jainism\"},{\"title\":\"Jain Ethics: Non-possession / Non-attachment (Aparigraha) Anuvrat : ) – ALL MEN MUST DIE\",\"url\":\"https://iwillgetmad.wordpress.com/category/jain-ethics-non-possession-non-attachment-aparigraha-anuvrat/\"},{\"title\":\"E-ISSN: 2581-8868 Volume-08, Issue-04, pp-55-60\",\"url\":\"https://theajhssr.com/vol-8-iss-4/THEAJHSSR_F0804055060010280.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Jainism - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jainism\"},{\"title\":\"Beyond Sustainable Economy: Non-Possession in Jaina Canonical Texts @ HereNow4U\",\"url\":\"https://www.herenow4u.net/index.php?id=131644\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's comprehensive information about Jain economics and the concept of aparigraha in relation to sustainable development:\n\n## Understanding Aparigraha\n\nIn Jainism, aparigraha is the virtue of non-possessiveness, non-grasping, or non-greediness. It means keeping the desire for possessions to what is necessary or important, which depends on one's life stage and context.\n\n## Limiting Consumption\n\nBy limiting personal consumption, Jain merchants accumulated surplus capital which was reinvested into the community rather than spent on lavish displays of wealth. Aparigraha brings forth a shift in perspective: namely, that limits to wealth accumulation, desires, and consumption are the only way to bring about lasting peace and happiness.\n\n## Connection to Sustainable Development\n\nAparigraha holds the answer to the problems emanating from rampant consumerism, i.e., the depletion of natural resources, climate change, and biodiversity loss, among others. Aparigraha inspires an individual to consume according to their needs, which prevents the unnecessary exploitation of resources and conserves natural capital.\n\n## Historical Economic Impact\n\nJain merchant guilds (mahajans) became dominant financial institutions in medieval and colonial India due to their reputation for ethical restraint. Wealth exceeding the limits set by one's Iccha-parimana vow is viewed not as personal property, but as a resource held in trust for the welfare of the wider society, leading to the proliferation of Jain-funded libraries, animal hospitals, and educational institutions.\n\n## Broader Philosophical Framework\n\nThe core of Jain philosophy is established on three ethical pillars: ahiṃsā (nonviolence), anekāntavāda (non-absolutism or many-sided reality), and aparigraha (non-possession).\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"9ae12da0-99ab-45ed-aef9-1f5e6a5f3752","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:29.816Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a4903e0b-3ea8-4f9b-a8d1-e4ba7a070558","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
