{"parentUuid":"ef491a47-7fec-42c6-a0ea-395f5acd1dca","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RwzFfyNKQyD8NJnHr23ff8","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"circular economy AI coordination regenerative economics doughnut economics 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Application of artificial intelligence in circular economy: A critical analysis of the current research - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2666188825003119\"},{\"title\":\"Mastering the circular economy and AI to stay competitive | World Economic Forum\",\"url\":\"https://www.weforum.org/stories/2025/08/why-you-must-master-the-circular-economy-and-ai-to-stay-competitive-by-2030/\"},{\"title\":\"Regenerative Business Accelerator 2025 - Bloom\",\"url\":\"https://bloom.pm/doughnut/\"},{\"title\":\"Circular Economy Platforms: A Systematic Review - Blackburn - 2026 - Business Strategy and the Environment - Wiley Online Library\",\"url\":\"https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/bse.70307\"},{\"title\":\"Selected publications - Circular Economy and Doughnut Economics - EC Library Guides at European Commission Library\",\"url\":\"https://ec-europa-eu.libguides.com/circular_economy_and_doughnut_economics/eu-publications/selected\"},{\"title\":\"Unlocking industrial decarbonization: the catalytic role of artificial intelligence in circular economy practices from EU countries | Humanities and Social Sciences Communications\",\"url\":\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41599-025-06230-8\"},{\"title\":\"Post-Growth, Degrowth, the Doughnut, and Circular Economy: A Short Guide for Policymakers | Journal of City Climate Policy and Economy\",\"url\":\"https://utppublishing.com/doi/10.3138/jccpe-2023-0004\"},{\"title\":\"Alternative Economic Models | DP IB Environmental Systems & Societies (ESS) Revision Notes 2024\",\"url\":\"https://www.savemyexams.com/dp/environmental-systems-and-societies-ess/ib/24/hl/revision-notes/1-foundation/1-3-sustainability/alternative-economic-models/\"},{\"title\":\"Doughnut Economics – A New Model for a Sustainable 21st-Century Economy - Regeneration Pioneers\",\"url\":\"https://www.regeneration-pioneers.com/en/2025/07/05/doughnut-economics-a-new-model-for-a-sustainable-21st-century-economy/\"},{\"title\":\"Designing a Regenerative Economy Starts with Creativity. And Doughnuts. - Magic Canoe\",\"url\":\"https://magiccanoe.org/designing-a-regenerative-economy-starts-with-creativity-and-doughnuts/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here are the key findings on circular economy, AI coordination, regenerative economics, and doughnut economics in 2025:\n\n## AI's Role in Circular Economy Coordination\n\nAI serves as the digital glue between circular economy actors, ensuring smooth coordination, real-time data sharing and adaptive decision-making. AI-based technologies such as predictive maintenance, supply chain optimization, and inventory management assist in predicting equipment failure, reducing downtime, extending the life span of equipment, reducing transport costs, and reducing overstock and waste.\n\nAI is the driving force to achieve circularity, and by 2030, AI will no longer be just a tool for improvement but will be the foundation for how decisions are made, how processes adapt in real time and how companies stay competitive.\n\n## Regenerative Economics Integration\n\nRecent work emphasizes more ambitious goals such as the regeneration of socio-ecological systems, with regeneration increasingly gaining traction within circular economy discourse as emphasis on the restoration and renewal of natural systems. Research is needed to explore how circular economy platforms can facilitate regenerative outcomes through design features, governance models, and coordination mechanisms.\n\n## Doughnut Economics Framework\n\nDoughnut Economics, developed by Kate Raworth, proposes a shift from a growth-focused economy to one that meets human needs within planetary boundaries, visualizing a safe and just space for humanity within a \"doughnut-shaped\" area. Many cities (e.g., Amsterdam, Brussels) and organizations are already experimenting with the Doughnut model for real-world decision-making.\n\n## 2025 Development\n\nA Fall 2025 Regenerative Business Accelerator is using the Doughnut Economics framework for a SF Bay Area hybrid program for climate, housing & social equity solutions.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"bf1650e0-af50-442d-9939-65fe3203bfb1","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:30.417Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ef491a47-7fec-42c6-a0ea-395f5acd1dca","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
