{"parentUuid":"d4142f5a-5b82-4813-92f5-ebbcaa2204f4","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01HttoaqEE26rRKNi29pEQzq","toolUseID":"toolu_01HttoaqEE26rRKNi29pEQzq","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:42.488Z","uuid":"47593a0f-6ebb-42b1-8ca3-05799e3f9505","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"456b02ee-c670-4f23-85a5-2d73b329deea","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HttoaqEE26rRKNi29pEQzq","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"AI coral reef restoration robotics Mars Coral program autonomous underwater monitoring 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Humans are working with robotics and AI to restore coral reefs at scale | AIMS\",\"url\":\"https://www.aims.gov.au/information-centre/news-and-stories/humans-are-working-robotics-and-ai-restore-coral-reefs-scale\"},{\"title\":\"Autonomous robotic systems for coral reef monitoring: Review and open research issues - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1574954125005205\"},{\"title\":\"AI-Driven Marine Robotics: Emerging Trends in Underwater Perception and Ecosystem Monitoring\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2509.01878v1\"},{\"title\":\"AI-driven Dispensing of Coral Reseeding Devices for Broad-scale Restoration of the Great Barrier Reef\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2509.01019v1\"},{\"title\":\"From Remote Sensing to Artificial Intelligence in Coral Reef Monitoring\",\"url\":\"https://www.mdpi.com/2075-1702/12/10/693\"},{\"title\":\"How Drones Are Revolutionizing Coral Reef Restoration (And Why It Works) - Marine Biodiversity Science Center\",\"url\":\"https://www.marinebiodiversity.ca/how-drones-are-revolutionizing-coral-reef-restoration-and-why-it-works/\"},{\"title\":\"A systematic review of robotic efficacy in coral reef monitoring techniques - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0025326X24002509\"},{\"title\":\"Top 10 Coral Startups Leading Reef Restoration Innovation in 2025\",\"url\":\"https://www.naturetechmemos.com/p/top-10-coral-startups-leading-reef-restoration-innovation-in-2025\"},{\"title\":\"REEF+ | CUREE Robot Uses AI for Coral Reef Restoration\",\"url\":\"https://globalfundcoralreefs.org/reef-plus/news/curee-robot-uses-ai-for-coral-reef-restoration/\"},{\"title\":\"Automated Robotic Platforms for Coral Reef Restoration in ...\",\"url\":\"https://iaeme.com/MasterAdmin/Journal_uploads/IJOE/VOLUME_5_ISSUE_1/IJOE_05_01_001.pdf\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results, here's what I found about AI coral reef restoration robotics and autonomous underwater monitoring in 2025:\n\n## Key Developments in Coral Reef Restoration\n\nThe Deployment Guidance System (DGS) combines the latest in marine robotics and artificial intelligence, with the aim to place young corals, housed in purpose-built devices, across the Reef in locations where they are likely to grow to adulthood.\n\nThe Reef Guidance System (RGS) is an AI model that classifies the reef substrate to determine suitable locations for coral devices to be deployed, runs on an edge camera unit which informs when to drop coral devices that are carried in the vessel, and performs automated substrate analysis and deployment decision-making in real-time at depths up to 10m.\n\n## Autonomous Monitoring Systems\n\nAutonomous Underwater Vehicles (AUVs) enable systematic, high-resolution, and non-invasive assessments over extensive and remote reef areas for comprehensive coral reef monitoring.\n\nThe ReefOS system combines static cameras, fish detection models, a custom photogrammetry toolkit, and a geospatial visualization dashboard to perform fine-scale monitoring of restoration sites in French Polynesia, Fiji and Thailand.\n\n## Recent Breakthroughs\n\nThe most promising projects combine elements from multiple methods—perhaps using automated propagation systems to grow genetically-selected coral varieties on advanced substrate materials, deployed by robotic systems and monitored with AI-powered imaging platforms.\n\nThe integration of artificial intelligence with drone technology has enabled automated marine monitoring systems that can assess reef health, track growth patterns, and identify areas requiring immediate intervention.\n\nThe search results show significant progress in integrating robotics, AI, and autonomous systems for both active coral restoration and comprehensive ecosystem monitoring in 2025.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"c31b6f56-27df-4f16-8269-be78627c31a4","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:42.488Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"456b02ee-c670-4f23-85a5-2d73b329deea","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"c31b6f56-27df-4f16-8269-be78627c31a4","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_017jPivKrX5LNduCvpfvfShx","toolUseID":"toolu_017jPivKrX5LNduCvpfvfShx","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:43.305Z","uuid":"4a45eb06-f021-4e83-9347-04c9ff63eb13","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"15b9714e-f10f-4ad6-810c-6c15e776d4d6","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017jPivKrX5LNduCvpfvfShx","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Carbon Direct MRV monitoring reporting verification AI machine learning carbon accounting 2025 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Monitoring, Reporting, and Verification (MRV) & Digital MRV (dMRV) in Carbon Projects - Anaxee Blog's\",\"url\":\"https://blog.anaxee.com/monitoring-reporting-and-verification-mrv-digital-mrv-dmrv-in-carbon-projects/\"},{\"title\":\"MRV and Digital MRV (Monitoring, Reporting, and Verification)\",\"url\":\"https://www.senken.io/glossary/mrv\"},{\"title\":\"Monitoring, Reporting, and Verification (MRV) & Digital MRV (dMRV) in Carbon Projects - Anaxee Digital Runners\",\"url\":\"https://anaxee.com/monitoring-reporting-and-verification-mrv-digital-mrv-dmrv-in-carbon-projects/\"},{\"title\":\"Carbon Management: Infrastructure Capable of Tracking CO₂\",\"url\":\"https://inspenet.com/en/articulo/carbon-management-and-mrv-systems/\"},{\"title\":\"What monitoring, reporting & verification (MRV) systems can reduce costs and enhance scalability of carbon farming? - ScienceDirect\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0301479726003452\"},{\"title\":\"Monitoring, Reporting, and Verification (MRV) Protocols Used in Carbon Trading Applied to Dryland Nations in the Global South for Climate Change Mitigation\",\"url\":\"https://www.mdpi.com/2071-1050/17/24/11001\"},{\"title\":\"MRV in Carbon Projects: Building Trust through Digital Measurement, Reporting, and Verification - Anaxee Digital Runners\",\"url\":\"https://anaxee.com/mrv-in-carbon-projects-building-trust-through-digital-measurement-reporting-and-verification/\"},{\"title\":\"Artificial Intelligence Techniques for Monitoring Carbon Emissions and Supporting Green Investment Decisions | International Journal of Environment and Climate Change\",\"url\":\"https://journalijecc.com/index.php/IJECC/article/view/5278\"},{\"title\":\"Case Study of Technology Adoption in Carbon Market ...\",\"url\":\"https://unfccc.int/sites/default/files/resource/MEP004_CfI_Addressing_Leakage_Mungroo.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Monitoring, reporting and verification (MRV) - Carbon Market Watch\",\"url\":\"https://carbonmarketwatch.org/glossary/monitoring-reporting-and-verification-mrv/\"}]\n\nI've successfully performed a web search for information about Carbon Direct MRV monitoring, reporting, verification, AI, machine learning, and carbon accounting for 2025-2026. Here are the key findings from recent sources:\n\n## Digital MRV and AI/Machine Learning Integration\n\nDigital MRV (dMRV) — powered by satellites, AI, sensors, and blockchain — promises faster, cheaper, and more transparent systems. Machine learning can make continuous monitoring the norm, and adopting AI technologies to automate the process to a fully integrated system requires building an end-to-end digital infrastructure, with investments already being made by Verra with its registry digitalization that uses built-in algorithms to automate calculations.\n\n## Key AI and Machine Learning Applications\n\nMachine-learning, deep-learning, and hybrid algorithms are significantly more effective in enhancing the accuracy of emission estimation, promoting close to real-time monitoring, and helping locate hotspots of emissions. AI models estimate biomass and soil carbon across landscapes.\n\n## Practical Improvements and Future Directions\n\nThe adoption of these solutions has enabled organizations to reduce the time required for external verifications by up to 60% and improve data accuracy by approximately 40%. AI-optimized sampling point layouts, AI-automated and online accessible data entry (besides project registration), and enhanced reporting standardization are being suggested for future implementation.\n\nFuture developments include machine learning making continuous monitoring the norm, open data platforms sharing dMRV data publicly to enhance market trust, and investors demanding real-time MRV dashboards before committing capital.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"103143b4-10d1-4bb0-9fd5-c86db5b138ec","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:43.305Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"15b9714e-f10f-4ad6-810c-6c15e776d4d6","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
