{"parentUuid":"143cb3a7-1e90-43b6-9dd2-8e9dc91e9984","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011ryTCe7hRW3pnUFHeWUv1r","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Grameen Bank microfinance AI automation digital lending developing countries 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"The Microcredit Business Model of Grameen Bank -AFCA\",\"url\":\"http://www.afca-asia.org/Portal.do?method=detailView&returnChannelID=3&contentID=1115\"},{\"title\":\"Grameen Bank - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grameen_Bank\"},{\"title\":\"Grameen Bank | microfinance, poverty alleviation, rural development | Britannica Money\",\"url\":\"https://www.britannica.com/money/Grameen-Bank\"},{\"title\":\"AI and ML Modeling and Autonomous Finance in Microfinance - Computational Intelligence for Autonomous Finance - Wiley Online Library\",\"url\":\"https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/9781394233250.ch9\"},{\"title\":\"\\\"A Reverse Technology Transfer:\\\" The Ford Foundation, Grameen Bank, and Microlending in the US - REsource\",\"url\":\"https://resource.rockarch.org/story/a-reverse-technology-transfer-the-ford-foundation-grameen-bank-and-microlending-in-the-us/\"},{\"title\":\"Microfinance Lending Market Size, Share | Industry Report 2035\",\"url\":\"https://www.marketresearchfuture.com/reports/microfinance-lending-market-24799\"},{\"title\":\"Grameen Bank: The Power of Microfinance - The Borgen Project\",\"url\":\"https://borgenproject.org/grameen-bank/\"},{\"title\":\"Grameen Bank - an overview | ScienceDirect Topics\",\"url\":\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/earth-and-planetary-sciences/grameen-bank\"},{\"title\":\"Digitizing microloan administration to fuel economic growth\",\"url\":\"https://www.kyndryl.com/us/en/customer-stories/interactive/grameen\"},{\"title\":\"Micro Lending Market Size, Share | Industry Report [2032]\",\"url\":\"https://www.fortunebusinessinsights.com/micro-lending-market-113621\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results, here's what I found about Grameen Bank, microfinance, AI automation, and digital lending in developing countries for 2025:\n\n## Grameen Bank Overview\n\nGrameen Bank is a microfinance specialized community development bank founded in Bangladesh that provides small loans to the impoverished without requiring collateral. Grameen Bank represents one of the largest, best performing, and most influencing microcredit financial institutions, whose business model has been emulated by many developing countries.\n\n## Digital Transformation and Automation in Microfinance\n\nThe microfinance sector is undergoing significant digital transformation. The Microfinance Lending Market is experiencing a dynamic shift towards digital solutions and social impact initiatives, with digital transformation reshaping the microfinance landscape and enhancing accessibility and efficiency.\n\nOrganizations are modernizing IT operations to include end-to-end digitization for loan administration tasks, and deploying core banking software capable of partially or fully automating loan processing stages.\n\n## AI and Automation Integration\n\nThe next evolution in Microfinance is through the adoption of Autonomous Finance, which integrates Artificial Intelligence (AI), Hyper Automation, and Data Management to redefine customer expectations and enhance operational efficiency.\n\nAI and data analytics are reshaping the market by revolutionizing risk assessment practices, making lending platforms more transparent, data-driven, and inclusive, and enabling microfinance institutes to evaluate creditworthiness using alternative data sources.\n\n## Market Growth Projections for 2025-2035\n\nThe Microfinance Lending industry is projected to grow from 301.99 USD Billion in 2025 to 813.72 USD Billion by 2035, exhibiting a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 10.42%.\n\nCompetitive trends in the Microfinance Lending Market as of October are increasingly defined by digitalization, sustainability, and the integration of artificial intelligence, with strategic alliances among key players shaping the landscape.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"281e2bff-887b-4c78-a2ca-cac90ca6e81b","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:44.267Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"143cb3a7-1e90-43b6-9dd2-8e9dc91e9984","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"281e2bff-887b-4c78-a2ca-cac90ca6e81b","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01YZ3HT1dadEKFEDcHFPnLiw","toolUseID":"toolu_01YZ3HT1dadEKFEDcHFPnLiw","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:44.433Z","uuid":"472bc744-c718-49fd-99f4-e6cbfca876cb","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"eebdcf97-f41a-49a0-85c1-6cf96cab0b25","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YZ3HT1dadEKFEDcHFPnLiw","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"social return on investment SROI metric comparison carbon offset welfare measurement 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Social Return on Investment (SROI) Calculator, Formula & Framework\",\"url\":\"https://www.sopact.com/use-case/social-return-on-invesment-sroi\"},{\"title\":\"Social return on investment - SROI\",\"url\":\"https://www.betterevaluation.org/methods-approaches/approaches/social-return-investment\"},{\"title\":\"Social return on investment - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_return_on_investment\"},{\"title\":\"Social Returns on Investment (SROI): A Guide to Measurement\",\"url\":\"https://blog.upmetrics.com/social-returns-on-investment\"},{\"title\":\"The Guide to SROI — Social Value International\",\"url\":\"https://www.socialvalueint.org/guide-to-sroi\"},{\"title\":\"IRIS+ and Social Return on Investment (SROI) | IRIS+\",\"url\":\"https://iris.thegiin.org/document/iris-and-social-return-on-investment/\"},{\"title\":\"Social Return on Investment (SROI): Measuring Tangible Impact with Doktar\",\"url\":\"https://www.doktar.com/en/blog/digital-agtech/social-return-on-investment-sroi-measuring-tangible-impact-with-doktar/\"},{\"title\":\"Application of Social Return on Investment (SROI) Method in Wetland Conservation | Journal of Human, Earth, and Future\",\"url\":\"https://www.hefjournal.org/index.php/HEF/article/view/612\"},{\"title\":\"SOCIAL RETURN ON INVESTMENT (SROI) - NEF Consulting\",\"url\":\"https://www.nefconsulting.com/what-we-do/evaluation-impact-assessment/sroi/\"},{\"title\":\"The social return on investment model: a systematic literature review | Meditari Accountancy Research | Emerald Publishing\",\"url\":\"https://www.emerald.com/medar/article/30/7/49/282355/The-social-return-on-investment-model-a-systematic\"}]\n\nI've completed a web search for your query on Social Return on Investment (SROI) metric comparison with carbon offset and welfare measurement. Here's what the search results reveal:\n\n## Overview of SROI\n\nSROI is a principles-based method for measuring extra-financial value (such as environmental or social value) not otherwise reflected or involved in conventional financial accounts. It is an outcomes-based measurement framework that assigns dollar values to social, environmental, and economic changes created by a program, then compares that total value against cost.\n\n## Metric Comparison and Applications\n\nThe search results show that SROI is widely applied across multiple domains. The sector legitimized by the SROI is mainly the welfare sector, particularly health, with 31 studies, social inclusion counting 13 studies and other sectors such as well-being, education and justice.\n\nFor carbon offset and environmental measurement specifically, a community reforestation program values carbon sequestration (carbon credit market prices), improved water quality (avoided treatment costs), biodiversity preservation (contingent valuation studies), and community recreation access (travel cost methods).\n\n## Key Challenges\n\nThe SROI model has limitations grouped into two main sets – lack of standardization and lack of resources – but has been identified as a tool to strengthen the collaboration and active involvement of organizations' stakeholders.\n\nThe search results provide general information about SROI frameworks and applications but don't contain detailed 2025-specific comparisons of SROI with other metrics for carbon offset and welfare measurement.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"42b5a9d8-3066-4539-b323-2587ce9a518b","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:21:44.433Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"eebdcf97-f41a-49a0-85c1-6cf96cab0b25","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
