{"parentUuid":"036c98c5-4ea1-4623-96a0-c4860e415be0","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JiDwdSYfH76UcDXbmM8Y3o","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Anthropic electricity pledge February 2026 carbon free energy AI data center\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Anthropic vows to protect consumers from rising electricity costs - SiliconANGLE\",\"url\":\"https://siliconangle.com/2026/02/11/anthropic-vows-protect-consumers-rising-electricity-costs/\"},{\"title\":\"Why is Anthropic Pledging to Offset its AI Energy Costs? | Sustainability Magazine\",\"url\":\"https://sustainabilitymag.com/news/why-anthropic-pledging-offset-ai-energy-costs\"},{\"title\":\"Trump's ratepayer protection pledge takes aim at AI energy bills | Fox News\",\"url\":\"https://www.foxnews.com/tech/what-trump-rate-payer-protection-pledge-means-you\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic says its datacenters won't spike your leccy bill • The Register\",\"url\":\"https://www.theregister.com/2026/02/12/anthropic_power_promises\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic Pledges 100% Grid Upgrade Funding to Offset AI Data Center Power Costs: 2026 Impact Analysis | AI News Detail\",\"url\":\"https://blockchain.news/ainews/anthropic-pledges-100-grid-upgrade-funding-to-offset-ai-data-center-power-costs-2026-impact-analysis\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic to cover costs of electricity price increases from its data centers\",\"url\":\"https://www.nbcnews.com/tech/tech-news/anthropic-cover-costs-electricity-price-increases-data-centers-rcna258554\"},{\"title\":\"Who is really footing the AI energy bill? Inside the debate about data center electricity costs\",\"url\":\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/03/13/ai-data-centers-electricity-prices-backlash-ratepayer-protection.html\"},{\"title\":\"Trump's Ratepayer Pledge: Big Tech Must Build Own Power | Introl Blog\",\"url\":\"https://introl.com/blog/trump-ratepayer-pledge-hyperscaler-self-generation\"},{\"title\":\"On The Path to 100% Clean Electricity May 2023\",\"url\":\"https://www.energy.gov/sites/default/files/2023-05/DOE%20-%20100%25%20Clean%20Electricity%20-%20Final.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"Anthropic promises to pay for electricity price increases due to it's AI data centers — firm to pay 100% of its grid infrastructure costs, produce new power sources as sector predicted to hit 50 GW in coming years | Tom's Hardware\",\"url\":\"https://www.tomshardware.com/tech-industry/artificial-intelligence/anthropic-promises-to-pay-for-electricity-price-increases-due-to-its-ai-data-centers-firm-to-pay-100-percent-of-its-grid-infrastructure-costs-produce-new-power-sources-as-sector-predicted-to-hit-50-gw-in-coming-years\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Anthropic's electricity pledge in February 2026:\n\n## Anthropic's February 2026 Electricity Pledge\n\nOn February 11, 2026, Anthropic announced that they will cover 100 percent of electricity price increases from their data centers, pay for all grid upgrades, and invest in new power and strain-reduction systems to protect ratepayers.\n\n### Key Commitments\n\nThe company will work with utilities providers to \"estimate and cover\" the likely price increases that will result from its data centers' massive consumption. The pledge applies specifically to facilities located in areas where it cannot generate enough new energy on its own, and Anthropic will foot the bill for the infrastructure upgrades that electricity providers need to make to connect its energy-intensive data centers to the power grid.\n\nAdditionally, Anthropic promised to procure new power sources to match its electricity needs and is investing in \"curtailment systems\" that will optimize its data centers' energy usage during periods of high demand, in order to minimize the impact of its consumption.\n\n### Political Context\n\nThough Anthropic's pledge is commendable, rivals including OpenAI Group PBC and Microsoft Corp. have made similar commitments to reduce the cost impact of their data centers. Anthropic joins rivals OpenAI and Microsoft in pledging to reduce the cost impacts of its data centers amid mounting political pressure on AI companies and data center operators.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"f6468847-e9fc-47dc-b038-3902d68c66d2","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:22:00.293Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"036c98c5-4ea1-4623-96a0-c4860e415be0","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
