{"parentUuid":"0f8f213f-62a6-4ae4-a6b8-a1b50cb6c437","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01NzFWzY2PxA1ieG81V9MHHx","toolUseID":"toolu_01NzFWzY2PxA1ieG81V9MHHx","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:22:15.981Z","uuid":"ca184159-4fed-49bb-84fc-39ba062c8ff2","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"405a4129-fd77-4743-99fb-360535b38d47","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NzFWzY2PxA1ieG81V9MHHx","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Sam Altman Universal Basic Income OpenAI compute access AI displaced workers 2025 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Sam Altman’s universal basic income experiment (OpenResearch) - Community - OpenAI Developer Community\",\"url\":\"https://community.openai.com/t/sam-altman-s-universal-basic-income-experiment-openresearch/877705\"},{\"title\":\"Here's what a Sam Altman-backed basic income experiment found - CBS News\",\"url\":\"https://www.cbsnews.com/news/sam-altman-universal-basic-income-study-open-research/\"},{\"title\":\"OpenAI's Sam Altman has a new idea for a universal basic income - Basic Income Canada Network\",\"url\":\"https://basicincomecanada.org/openais-sam-altman-has-a-new-idea-for-a-universal-basic-income/\"},{\"title\":\"UBI Study Backed by OpenAI's Sam Altman Bolsters Support for Basic Income - Bloomberg\",\"url\":\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-07-22/ubi-study-backed-by-openai-s-sam-altman-bolsters-support-for-basic-income\"},{\"title\":\"If AI Puts Everyone Out of Work, Is UBI the Solution?\",\"url\":\"https://www.governing.com/finance/if-ai-puts-everyone-out-of-work-is-ubi-the-solution\"},{\"title\":\"OpenAI's Sam Altman has a new idea for a universal basic income\",\"url\":\"https://www.yahoo.com/tech/openais-sam-altman-idea-universal-213637146.html\"},{\"title\":\"Meet the woman running Sam Altman's UBI study | Fortune\",\"url\":\"https://fortune.com/2024/02/09/sam-altman-ubi-study-elizabeth-rhodes-openai-openresearch/\"},{\"title\":\"OpenAI's Sam Altman: AI-Generated Wealth Will Enable a $13,500-a-Year Basic Income - Slashdot\",\"url\":\"https://yro.slashdot.org/story/21/03/27/0116241/openais-sam-altman-ai-generated-wealth-will-enable-a-13500-a-year-basic-income\"},{\"title\":\"Sam Altman envisions a future where universal basic income is a \\\"slice of GPT\\\" | TechSpot\",\"url\":\"https://www.techspot.com/news/102975-sam-altman-envisions-future-where-universal-basic-income.html\"},{\"title\":\"OpenAI CEO Sam Altman Has An Idea To Help Everyone Get ‘Universal Basic Income’ - DesignTAXI.com\",\"url\":\"https://designtaxi.com/news/426734/OpenAI-CEO-Sam-Altman-Has-An-Idea-To-Help-Everyone-Get-Universal-Basic-Income/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Sam Altman's initiatives regarding universal basic income, compute access, and AI-displaced workers:\n\n## Universal Basic Income Research\n\nSam Altman and other AI researchers have for nearly a decade worried that artificial intelligence technology could one day be good enough to make many knowledge workers, even coders, obsolete. To investigate potential solutions, OpenAI backed OpenResearch, a project that distributed $1,000 monthly to beneficiaries in Illinois and Texas for three years.\n\nThe study found that recipients spend more to meet their basic needs and assist others, and don't drop out of the workforce — although they work slightly fewer hours.\n\n## Universal Basic Compute\n\nRather than just cash transfers, \"Universal basic compute\" was Altman's concept where \"Everybody gets like a slice of GPT-7's compute,\" as he stated on the All-In podcast. The idea is that as AI becomes advanced and embedded into more facets of our lives, owning a unit of a large language model like GPT-7 can be more valuable than money, allowing people to use it, resell it, or donate it for research.\n\n## AI and Job Displacement Concerns\n\nAltman's interest in universal basic income is related to his work as CEO of OpenAI—if AI eliminates jobs, could guaranteed cash help workers who lose their income? In 2021, Altman said he believed AI could generate enough wealth to pay every U.S. adult $13,500 a year.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"95f5e854-aadc-49d4-8850-a742657656b1","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:22:15.981Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"405a4129-fd77-4743-99fb-360535b38d47","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"95f5e854-aadc-49d4-8850-a742657656b1","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01AyRuiyhJjHrFp57e2LMdpE","toolUseID":"toolu_01AyRuiyhJjHrFp57e2LMdpE","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:22:16.973Z","uuid":"4268341b-d4f7-479b-991b-8f098a719726","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"9a4e812b-2290-4fe9-865e-888b70a1ebe1","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"6e08ca5d-55d5-45b5-94b3-47bc722de092","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AyRuiyhJjHrFp57e2LMdpE","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"regenerative agriculture AI precision soil carbon restoration scale global potential 2025 2026\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Scaling Sustainable Farming: AgreenaCarbon’s 2.3 Million Verified Carbon Credits Redefine Regenerative Agriculture • Carbon Credits\",\"url\":\"https://carboncredits.com/scaling-sustainable-farming-agreenacarbons-2-3-million-verified-carbon-credits-redefine-regenerative-agriculture/\"},{\"title\":\"Delivering regenerative agriculture through digitalization and AI | World Economic Forum\",\"url\":\"https://www.weforum.org/stories/2025/01/delivering-regenerative-agriculture-through-digitalization-and-ai/\"},{\"title\":\"7 Regenerative Practices To Boost Soil Health In 2026\",\"url\":\"https://farmonaut.com/blogs/7-regenerative-practices-to-boost-soil-health-in-2026\"},{\"title\":\"3 Ways To Make Agriculture More Sustainable In 2026\",\"url\":\"https://farmonaut.com/precision-farming/3-ways-to-make-agriculture-more-sustainable-in-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Carbon Farming: 7 Carbon Capture & Sequestration Breakthroughs\",\"url\":\"https://farmonaut.com/blogs/carbon-farming-7-carbon-capture-sequestration-breakthroughs\"},{\"title\":\"Frontiers | Quantifying soil carbon sequestration from regenerative agricultural practices in crops and vineyards\",\"url\":\"https://www.frontiersin.org/journals/sustainable-food-systems/articles/10.3389/fsufs.2023.1234108/full\"},{\"title\":\"Agricultural Biosolutions: AI & Runoff Solutions 2026\",\"url\":\"https://farmonaut.com/blogs/agricultural-biosolutions-ai-runoff-solutions-2026\"},{\"title\":\"Top 5 AgTech Trends for 2025: What’s Next for Regenerative Agriculture? - Global Ag Tech Initiative\",\"url\":\"https://www.globalagtechinitiative.com/digital-farming/top-5-agtech-trends-for-2025-whats-next-for-regenerative-agriculture/\"},{\"title\":\"AI-Optimized Regenerative Agriculture: Accelerating Soil Carbon Sequestration for Climate Action | Springer Nature Link (formerly SpringerLink)\",\"url\":\"https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-032-05745-7_19\"},{\"title\":\"Differential impacts of regenerative agriculture practices on soil organic carbon: a meta-analysis of studies from India | Scientific Reports\",\"url\":\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-025-12149-6\"}]\n\nBased on the web search results, here's what I found about regenerative agriculture, AI, precision soil carbon restoration, and their global potential for 2025-2026:\n\n## Market Growth and Investment\n\nThe regenerative agriculture market is poised for rapid expansion, with an estimated market size of USD 9.2 billion in 2025 and projected growth to USD 18.3 billion by 2030, reflecting a 14.75% compound annual growth rate. Major food and beverage companies are investing heavily in regenerative sourcing, with Nestlé pledging CHF 1.2 billion to source half its priority materials from regenerative farms by 2030, while PepsiCo is funding USD 216 million to transition 7 million acres.\n\n## AI-Driven Measurement and Verification\n\nCompanies like Agreena use AI-driven digital measurement, reporting, and verification (dMRV) to rigorously verify the impact of regenerative practices and offer corporates access to high-quality nature-based carbon offsets. By leveraging satellite imagery, machine learning, and sensor networks, dMRV systems verify carbon credits with accurate, field-level data, preventing fraud, boosting transparency, and helping farmers adopt practices faster.\n\n## AI Investment and Growth\n\nAI in agriculture is projected to grow from $1.7 billion in 2023 to $4.7 billion by 2028, while digital agriculture could boost the agricultural GDP of low- and middle-income countries by more than $450 billion, or 28% per annum.\n\n## Key Technologies and Practices\n\nAdvanced monitoring systems integrate data from satellites, drones and soil maps to guide the targeted application of crop protection products and detect diseases and pests early. AI-driven techniques, such as real-time monitoring and predictive modeling, substantially improve practices such as no-till farming and biochar application.\n\n## Soil Carbon Sequestration Validation\n\nOver 1.1 million tonnes of CO₂ have been captured and stored in soils through verified regenerative agriculture projects, matching the yearly carbon footprint of 90,000 individuals. As carbon disclosure requirements tighten and environmental incentives expand, global momentum is expected to grow in 2026 and beyond.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"a9d8c200-db63-40bf-b4a1-11107d90b0e8","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:22:16.973Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"9a4e812b-2290-4fe9-865e-888b70a1ebe1","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"a9d8c200-db63-40bf-b4a1-11107d90b0e8","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"PostToolUse","hookName":"PostToolUse:WebSearch","command":"bash \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/hooks/run-with-flags-shell.sh\" \"post:observe\" \"skills/continuous-learning-v2/hooks/observe.sh\" \"standard,strict\""},"parentToolUseID":"toolu_01DBQUP6WP8VXgyDqogdNtmM","toolUseID":"toolu_01DBQUP6WP8VXgyDqogdNtmM","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:22:18.727Z","uuid":"f615a9b0-3ec6-4526-8e1b-e0357fb6d9ef","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"1341ec42-af28-4a0a-a936-07c4b53a9724","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"6e08ca5d-55d5-45b5-94b3-47bc722de092","agentId":"adb9276692a3e70f3","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DBQUP6WP8VXgyDqogdNtmM","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"B Corp impact measurement metrics comparison ESG sustainability reporting beyond profit 2025\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Measuring Environmental Impact for B Corp™ Certification Guide\",\"url\":\"https://www.sweep.net/pdf/sweep_guide_bcorp_v8-5483.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"B Corp vs IMPACT CERTIFIED: Choosing the Right Sustainability Framework\",\"url\":\"https://future-plus.co.uk/resources/practical-guide-to-esg-2/\"},{\"title\":\"ESC Standards, Simplified - B Lab U.S. & Canada - B Corp\",\"url\":\"https://usca.bcorporation.net/environmental-stewardship-and-circularity-standards-simplified/\"},{\"title\":\"B Corp Certification | Greenplaces\",\"url\":\"https://greenplaces.com/regulation/b-corp-certification/\"},{\"title\":\"B Corps outperforming ordinary businesses, new data shows\",\"url\":\"https://bcorporation.uk/news-stories-and-events/news/b-corps-outperforming-ordinary-businesses-new-data-shows/\"},{\"title\":\"Section 3: The B Impact Assessment | Business Sustainability Collaborative\",\"url\":\"https://bsc.poole.ncsu.edu/b-corporations/bcorp-handbook-guide-section3/\"},{\"title\":\"Corporate Environmental, Social, and Governance Performance: The Impacts on Financial Returns, Business Model Innovation, and Social Transformation\",\"url\":\"https://www.mdpi.com/2071-1050/17/3/1286\"},{\"title\":\"Measuring environmental impact for B Corp™ certification - Sweep\",\"url\":\"https://www.sweep.net/insights/measuring-environmental-impact-for-b-corp-certification\"},{\"title\":\"Get started with B Impact™\",\"url\":\"https://www.bcorporation.net/en-us/programs-and-tools/b-impact/\"},{\"title\":\"How Does a B Corp Measure Its Financial Return Alongside Its Social Impact? → Learn\",\"url\":\"https://esg.sustainability-directory.com/learn/how-does-a-b-corp-measure-its-financial-return-alongside-its-social-impact/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's comprehensive information about B Corp impact measurement metrics, ESG sustainability reporting, and going beyond profit in 2025:\n\n## 2025 B Corp Standards Update\n\nIn April 2025, B Lab published a major revision of its standards requiring companies to meet minimum performance thresholds across seven core impact topics and to build a roadmap for ongoing improvement rather than rely solely on past scores. The updated 2025 Standards introduce baseline requirements across 10 key impact areas, notably including the Climate Action Pillar.\n\n## Key Impact Measurement Areas\n\nThese will set out minimum standards for all B Corps to meet across impact areas including human rights, workplace culture, fair wages, climate action and environmental stewardship. The self-assessment section of B Impact gives an overview of the seven Impact Topic areas, from climate action to human rights, so you can benchmark your impact and discover the requirements for B Corp Certification.\n\n## Environmental Metrics and Climate Action\n\nUnder the 2025 Standards, every Certified B Corporation must measure and publicly disclose their greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions footprint, create a climate action plan aligned with a 1.5. Micro-enterprises must report GHG emissions and publish a climate transition plan. Mid-sized and large companies must additionally set validated science-based targets aligned with the SBTi.\n\nESG reporting coverage across operations and the supply chain, progress against reduction targets for water, energy, greenhouse gas emissions, and land use, and ratio of revenue from products or services aligned with ecological thresholds (e.g., low-carbon, water-efficient, circular by design) help ensure your strategy isn't just a plan on paper, but a system of ongoing accountability and measurable progress.\n\n## Measurement Tools and Integration\n\nB Lab's B Impact Assessment (BIA) is a publicly available impact measurement tool whereby any company can measure and manage their ESG performance. B Corps use integrated reporting to track financial metrics alongside BIA scores and mission-related social impact KPIs.\n\nB Corps can benefit from the SASB standards, which offer industry-specific reporting guidance. These standards enable companies to disclose material environmental, social, and governance (ESG) information relevant to their specific industry.\n\n## Beyond Profit Perspective\n\nCorporate sustainability performance becomes the central element in many current business developments: the total value of ESG investment grows, more and more clients want to invest in projects that deliver more than the pure financial return, companies are innovating and transforming their business models, and adopting the B-Corp values.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"36187199-40bf-4d09-89f5-be8f4515ae4b","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:22:18.727Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"1341ec42-af28-4a0a-a936-07c4b53a9724","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
